{{see|may}}
==English==

===Etymology===
From Middle English < Old English < Old French '''[[mai]]''' < Latin '''[[Maius]]''' (Maia's month) < '''[[Maia]]''', a Roman earth goddess (daughter of [[Atlas]] and wife of [[Vulcan]]) whose name is possibly from Proto-Indo-European '''[[*magya]]''' (she who is great) < PIE base '''[[*meg-]]''' (great).

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-May.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Proper noun===
'''May'''

# The fifth [[month]] of the [[Gregorian calendar]], having 31 [[day]]s.
#:'''Last:''' [[April]]
#:'''Next:''' [[June]]
# (''alternative spelling'' '''Mae''') A female [[given name]].
# A [[surname]].

====Usage notes====
'''May''' is often spelled '''[[Mae]]''' in conjoined names [''[[e.g.]], Lillie Mae, Katie Mae, Fannie Mae,...''], and can also be spelled that way when used alone.

